<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="580" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[130,777,631,1198]" box="[132,277,631,657]" pageId="19" pageNumber="580">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[130,777,631,1198]" pageId="19" pageNumber="580">
Ramose colonies, branch diameter 3.0- 
<quantity box="[573,668,662,688]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="19" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
. Exozone distinct, 
<quantity box="[236,373,694,721]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.5">0.5-0.6 mm</quantity>
wide, endozone 2.0- 
<quantity box="[615,707,694,720]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="19" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
wide. Autozooecia long, growing parallel to branch axis for a long distance in endozone and bending sharply in exozone, having rounded-polygonal shape in transverse section in endozone. Autozooecial apertures oval to polygonal. Autozooecial diaphragms thin, planar, widely spaced in endozone; common to abundant in exozone, planar, rarely inclined, developed as extension of wall cortex. Mesozooecia arising in endozone, polygonal in transverse section, 2-6 surrounding each autozooecial aperture. Mesozooecial diaphragms planar, densely spaced. Acanthostyles absent. Autozooecial walls indistinctly laminated, 
<quantity box="[254,442,1045,1072]" metricMagnitude="-6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="0.0065" valueMax="0.008" valueMin="0.005">
<geoCoordinate box="[254,318,1045,1072]" degrees="0.005" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="580" precision="55" value="0.005">0.005</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[318,389,1045,1072]" degrees="0.008" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="19" pageNumber="580" precision="55" value="-0.008">-0.008</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
thick in endozone; displaying distinct reverse V-shaped structure with dark autozooecial boundary, with weakly developed wall cortex continued in diaphragms, 
<quantity box="[272,428,1141,1167]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="580" unit="mm" value="0.08" valueMax="0.12" valueMin="0.04">0.04-0.12 mm</quantity>
thick in exozone. Maculae indistinct, consisting of macrozooecia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[130,776,1236,1582]" box="[132,277,1236,1262]" pageId="19" pageNumber="580">COMPARISON</paragraph>
